                     <interp inst="t18331017-22-person337" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer and live at No. 4, Lighthorn-court, Bell-alley. I was standing at the end of Coleman-street, and heard a noise in the Old Jewry; I ran up and saw Roe holding the prisoner - he said he had picked a gentleman's pocket - I received the handkerchief from him, and went after the prosecutor, and asked him of he had lost a handkerchief - he was not conscious of it at the time - he said it had a cross in the middle of it, and claimed it.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I throw myself on the mercy of the Court; it is the first offence I have been guilty of.</p>
